      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ASTON GOSSET (1) has been beaten for early speed lately, last time finishing eighth (26.93) in a Bottom Up - Restricted Win at Warrnambool. Form from his last run is proving strong. Has ability and is a key runner. PUDDIN' CAKE (8) pinged the lids last start from an awkward draw and led throughout to score (18.18) at this track in a TG1-4W over 305m. Has good speed and will be prominent from out wide. Leading chance again. SAINT ELLA (2) broke from the inside draw and filled a minor placing last start, beaten only half a length (18.21) behind PUDDIN' CAKE at this track. Must be included in calculations. STICKY FINGERS (5) hasn't been far away, finishing in the money twice in a row including last time in a TG1-4W at this track over 305m. Safe beginner who will go forward from trap two.",
